cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL

This paper deals with the study and automatic processing of 17th century English language, which involves morphosyntactic analysis and the use of electronic dictionaries. This falls under the scope of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and natural language processing (cs.LG). The proposed method of transcription using transducers and electronic dictionaries involves machine learning techniques and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of rules and algorithms for transcription also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL) techniques.
